excerpt: 1 of the country's tallest, this landmark building houses the Tango Museum, offices & residences.
detail_description: Palacio Salvo is one of the tallest landmarks in the country and houses the Tango Museum, offices, and residences. It's located near Mercado del Puerto, a lively area filled with local cuisine and live music. Other recommended stops in the city include Palacio Legislativo, Teatro Solis, and Fortaleza for stunning views of the city. The gothic-style building was constructed by an Italian immigrant and opened in 1928.
name: Palacio Salvo
address: Pl. Independencia 848, 11100 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Ciudad Vieja draws visitors for its history and cultural museums and grand, centuries-old landmarks. These include the neoclassical Metropolitan Cathedral, which overlooks quaint Plaza Matriz, and Solis Theatre with its diverse performing arts program. Lively steakhouses fill up quickly at the Mercado del Puerto indoor market. The area is also a nightlife hub, offering a mix of hip cocktail bars and old-school cafes.
detail_description: Ciudad Vieja, a historic neighborhood in Montevideo, is a popular destination for its rich cultural heritage and well-preserved landmarks. The area boasts the neoclassical Metropolitan Cathedral and the Solis Theatre, known for its diverse performing arts program. Visitors can explore quaint Plaza Matriz and enjoy lively steakhouses at Mercado del Puerto indoor market. This district also offers a vibrant nightlife scene with trendy cocktail bars and traditional cafes.
name: Ciudad Vieja
address: 11000 Montevideo, Montevideo Department, Uruguay

detail_description: Mercado del Puerto, located at Piedras 237, is a must-visit spot in Montevideo offering a blend of gastronomic delights and cultural experiences. Housed in a historic building that once served as the city's main market for produce and meats, this place boasts stunning architecture and rich history. While it can be a bit pricey, it's renowned for its local specialty Medio y Medio, a sweet sparkling white wine.
name: Mercado del Puerto
address: Rambla 25 de Agosto de 1825 228, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: This popular city beach is known for its lively boardwalk, sweeping views & beachfront activities.
detail_description: De los Pocitos Beach, located in Montevideo, is a popular city beach known for its lively boardwalk, golden sands, and picturesque promenade. It offers visitors the chance to unwind and enjoy activities such as beach volleyball, sunbathing, and leisurely strolls against the backdrop of the glistening waters of the River Plate.
name: De los Pocitos Beach
address: Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Municipal art museum in a stately 1870 villa featuring extensive Uruguayan works & formal gardens.
detail_description: Nestled in the charming neighborhood of Prado, Museo Juan Manuel Blanes is a municipal art museum housed in a grand 1870 villa. It boasts an extensive collection of Uruguayan artworks spanning different eras. The museum pays homage to the renowned Uruguayan portrait artist and Realist painter, Juan Manuel Blanes, also known as the "Painter of the Homeland." Visitors can admire his significant works alongside pieces by other influential artists like Pedro Figari and Rafael Barradas.
name: Museo Juan Manuel Blanes
address: Av. Millán 4015, 11700 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Montevideo, Uruguay’s capital, is a major city along Montevideo Bay. It revolves around the Plaza de la Independencia, once home to a Spanish citadel. This plaza leads to Ciudad Vieja (the old town), with art deco buildings, colonial homes and landmarks including the towering Palacio Salvo and neoclassical performance hall Solís Theatre. Mercado del Puerto is an old port market filled with many steakhouses.
detail_description: Montevideo, the capital of Uruguay, is a vibrant city located along Montevideo Bay. The Plaza de la Independencia leads to Ciudad Vieja, where you can find a mix of art deco buildings and colonial homes, as well as iconic landmarks like the Palacio Salvo and Solís Theatre. The old port market, Mercado del Puerto, is filled with numerous steakhouses offering delicious local cuisine.
name: Montevideo
address: Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Open-air, Sunday flea market selling antique silverware, second-hand books & pre-loved fashions.
detail_description: The Feria de Tristan Narvaja is a vibrant open-air flea market that takes place every Sunday along the street of the same name. Visitors can explore a wide variety of items, including antique silverware, second-hand books, and pre-loved fashion. While there are limited food options available, the market offers an abundance of fresh fruits and vegetables. Additionally, unique finds such as artisanal beers and traditional wooden crafts can be discovered while strolling through the bustling stalls.
name: Feria de Tristan Narvaja
address: Dr. Tristán Narvaja 1545, 11200 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Museum featuring pieces by Uruguayan artist, Torres García, known for his cubist paintings.
detail_description: The Torres Garcia's Museum, located in Ciudad Vieja, is a tribute to the renowned Uruguayan artist Joaquin Torres Garcia. The museum showcases an impressive collection of his cubist paintings, sculptures, and workshops that offer insight into his profound influence on modernism. It appeals to art connoisseurs and history enthusiasts interested in delving into Uruguay's cultural heritage. Visitors are encouraged to take their time appreciating the intricate details and symbolism in Torres Garcia's artworks.
name: Torres Garcia's Museum
address: Sarandí 683, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Parque Rodó is a laid-back residential area centered on its namesake green space, which has a boating lake and vintage amusement park rides. Also in the park, the National Museum of Visual Arts features 20th-century Uruguayan paintings and a sculpture garden. Nearby, Ramírez Beach is lined with bars and steakhouses overlooking the Río de la Plata. The Teatro de Verano stages outdoor rock shows and plays in summer.
detail_description: Parque Rodó is a relaxed neighborhood known for its namesake park, which offers a boating lake and classic amusement park attractions. The National Museum of Visual Arts, located within the park, showcases 20th-century Uruguayan artwork and boasts a sculpture garden. Ramírez Beach, situated nearby along the Río de la Plata, features bars and steakhouses with scenic views. During the summer months, Teatro de Verano hosts outdoor rock concerts and theatrical performances.
name: Parque Rodó
address: Montevideo, Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Guided tours of marbled chambers in a neoclassical building housing the Uruguayan parliament.
detail_description: Palacio Legislativo, a neoclassical building that serves as the home of the Uruguayan parliament, is a symbol of national pride and democratic values. Declared a National Historic Monument in 1975, this monumental structure was inaugurated in 1925 to commemorate Uruguay's independence. The palace features luxurious offices and houses numerous masterpieces by renowned artists such as Pedro Blanes and Jose Luis Zorrilla.
name: Palacio Legislativo
address: 4R57+G35, Av. de las Leyes, 11800 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt:
Pocitos is also the colloquial name for the city of Salvador Mazza, Salta Province, Argentina
Pocitos is an upscale seaside barrio of Montevideo, Uruguay. It borders Buceo to the east, Parque Batlle to the north, Tres Cruces, Cordón and Parque Rodó to the west and Punta Carretas to the south. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Pocitos is a vibrant and upscale seaside neighborhood in Montevideo, Uruguay. Its name, meaning 'little wells,' reflects its history as a clay extraction site. Today, it's known for its buzzing nightlife, art-deco architecture, and sultry tango rhythms. The area boasts Pocitos Beach and two bustling shopping avenues that attract families and friends of all ages.
name: Pocitos
address: 11300 Montevideo, Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Spanish fortress housing a military museum on a large hill overlooking the Bay of Montevideo.
detail_description: Fortaleza del Cerro, also known as Fortress Hill, is a historic Spanish fortress located on the highest hill in Montevideo. Built in 1809 to defend against naval attacks, it now houses a military museum showcasing Uruguay's defense history. The fortress offers panoramic views of Montevideo Bay and features a 19th-century lighthouse.
name: Fortaleza del Cerro
address: José Batlle y Ordóñez S/N, Cerro de Montevideo, 12802 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Grand 19th-century market building filled with bustling, meat-centric restaurants & bars.
detail_description: Established in 1868, Mercado del Puerto, also known as Port Market, is situated in the port of Old Town Montevideo. It has become a popular spot for locals to gather, shop, and dine on weekends. The market features various stalls offering a wide range of products including accessories, food ingredients, and clothing. Visitors can also enjoy traditional Uruguayan beef barbeque known as Parilla de Carne Uruguaya at this vibrant marketplace.
name: Port Market
address: Piedras 237, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Private museum with exhibits about the 1972 Andes plane crash & tributes to its victims & survivors.
detail_description: Museo Andes 1972 is a private museum that opened in 2013, dedicated to the tragic story of the 1972 Andes plane crash. The museum features exhibits that recount the details of the crash and pay tribute to its victims and survivors. It aims to raise awareness about this national tragedy and the struggle for survival in one of the world's tallest and coldest mountains.
name: Museo Andes 1972
address: Rincón 619, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Cultural center housed in a unique castle dating to 1911, with guided tours & spiritual workshops.
detail_description: The Castillo del Alquimista, also known as the Castillo Pittamiglio, is a 1911 architectural landmark located in the town of Città di Castello, Province of Perugia, Italy. The museum features guided tours and spiritual workshops.
name: Universo Pittamiglio - Castillo del Alquimista
address: Rbla. Mahatma Gandhi 633, 11300 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Brick lighthouse built in the late 19th century, with an attached keeper's house.
detail_description: The Punta Carretas Lighthouse, a historic brick structure with an attached keeper's house, is a must-visit attraction in Montevideo, Uruguay. Built in the late 19th century and standing at 59 meters tall, it offers visitors a chance to delve into Uruguay's maritime history while enjoying stunning panoramic views of the city and coastline.
name: Punta Carretas Lighthouse
address: 3R7Q+WQX, 11300 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Museum with extravagant costumes & masks chronicling the annual carnival, plus an open-air stage.
detail_description: The Museo del Carnaval in Montevideo is a vibrant museum showcasing the annual carnival with its extravagant costumes, masks, and open-air stage. It offers a comprehensive overview of the colorful event, featuring past parade floats, costumes, and an evocative photographic exhibition documenting the evolution of celebrations. The museum provides insight into Uruguay's capital city's 40-day-long carnival celebration with drum troupes, samba dancing, and murgas across 16 neighborhoods.
name: Museo del Carnaval
address: Rambla 25 de Agosto de 1825 218, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Monumental city cathedral, begun in 1790, featuring neoclassical architecture & several tombs.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Ciudad Vieja, the Montevideo Metropolitan Cathedral stands as a stunning testament to neoclassical architecture and rich history. Established in 1790 on the site of an earlier parish church, this magnificent Roman Catholic cathedral serves as the spiritual hub for Montevideo's Catholic community. With its striking twin bell towers and grand central dome, it captures the essence of colonial elegance.
name: Montevideo Metropolitan Cathedral
address: Ituzaingó 1373, 11100 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Celebrated market offering local produce & groceries, gift shops, specialty stores & a food court.
detail_description: The Mercado Agrícola de Montevideo, also known as MAM, is a vibrant gastronomic destination that offers a wide array of experiences. Visitors can explore and purchase fresh local produce, farm products, and artisanal organic or gourmet delights. The market also features gift shops, specialty stores, and a food court where families can enjoy a leisurely lunch. On weekends, the culinary experience is enhanced with live music and orchestras adding cultural value to the dining atmosphere.
name: Mercado Agrícola de Montevideo
address: José L. Terra 2220, 11800 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: When visiting Montevideo, don't miss the iconic Montevideo sign located in Carlos Vaz Ferreira Park. This popular tourist attraction offers a perfect backdrop for capturing stunning photographs with the city's landmarks and emblems. Situated along the picturesque Rambla de Montevideo, it provides a unique view of the beach and luxurious ocean-facing apartments. Due to its popularity, it's advisable to arrive early to avoid long waiting times for that perfect photo opportunity.
name: Montevideo sign
address: 4P6R+F94, Av. José Batlle y Ordóñez, 12800 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: 20th-century French-style palace, once a private home, now housing the Museum of Decorative Arts.
detail_description: Palacio Taranco, situated in the Ciudad Vieja district, is a 20th-century French-style palace that was once a private residence and now serves as the Museum of Decorative Arts. Originally built by the wealthy Taranco family, it stands on the site of the colonial Casa de Comedias and showcases opulence from the Belle Epoque era.
name: Palacio Taranco
address: Circunvalación Durango Entre, 1 de Mayo y, 11100 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Trendy, expansive market highlighting global food & grocery stalls, plus wine & beer.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Cordon neighborhood, Mercado Ferrando is a must-visit destination for food lovers and social butterflies alike. This expansive market showcases an array of global culinary delights alongside local Uruguayan specialties, making it a true gastronomic adventure. From spicy dishes to sweet desserts, hearty pastas to sizzling pizzas, there's something to satisfy every palate. The market's design encourages social interaction, providing cozy spaces for friends to gather or meet new ones.
name: Mercado Ferrando
address: Chaná 2120, 11200 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Cultural space in a converted 1800s prison featuring exhibitions of contemporary art.
detail_description: Immerse yourself in the world of contemporary art at the Contemporary Art Space, located within a converted 1800s prison. This unique cultural space showcases thought-provoking art pieces by local artists, offering a diverse range of mediums including video projections, paintings, and 3-D demonstrations. As you wander through the galleries, you'll not only appreciate the artistic talent but also experience a piece of history within the former Miguelete prison.
name: Contemporary Art Space
address: Arenal Grande 1930, 11800 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: The upscale residential suburb of Carrasco has a long stretch of beach backed by an elegant promenade, around which a cluster of hotels, bars, and restaurants form the area’s lively core. Inland, leafy streets feature a mix of well-preserved early-20th-century houses and independent, long-standing antiques shops and bookstores. General Lavalleja Park is popular for strolls, jogs, and picnics beside Carrasco Creek.
detail_description: Carrasco is an upscale residential suburb known for its long beach and elegant promenade, surrounded by hotels, bars, and restaurants. The area features well-preserved early-20th-century houses, independent antique shops, and bookstores along leafy streets. General Lavalleja Park offers a popular spot for leisure activities beside Carrasco Creek.
name: Carrasco
address: Montevideo, Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Upscale coastal district Punta Carretas is home to Faro de Punta Brava, a working 1870s lighthouse with sea views. Casual eateries and rocky beaches line Rambla Gandhi, a popular waterfront promenade. Inland, Juan Zorrilla de San Martín Park has picnic spots and a handicrafts fair. A whimsical mishmash of architectural styles, from medieval to modernist, Pittamiglio Castle hosts theater and magic shows.
detail_description: Punta Carretas, an upscale coastal district in Montevideo, offers a blend of historical and modern attractions. Visitors can explore the working 1870s Faro de Punta Brava lighthouse with stunning sea views or stroll along the popular waterfront promenade, Rambla Gandhi, lined with casual eateries and rocky beaches. Inland, Juan Zorrilla de San Martín Park provides picnic spots and hosts a handicrafts fair.
name: Punta Carretas
address: 11300 Montevideo, Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Ornate, monumental theater built in 1856 offering a diverse performing arts program & public tours.
detail_description: The Solis Theater, a monumental venue built in 1856 by the Italian architect Carlo Zucchi, is a significant landmark in Montevideo's Old Town. With a capacity of 1,100 spectators, it offers a diverse performing arts program including theater, ballet, opera and concerts. After undergoing refurbishment and reopening in 2004, this elegant theater with superb acoustics has become Montevideo's premier performance space.
name: Solis Theater
address: 3QRX+WHR, Reconquista S / N esq, Bartolomé Mitre, 11000 Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Museum in opulent 19th-century mansion, with statues, art, furniture & displays on ranching life.
detail_description: Nestled within the stunning 19th-century Palacio Heber Jackson, the Museo del Gaucho and Currency offers a captivating glimpse into the life of South America's iconic gauchos. This museum beautifully illustrates their profound bond with horses and showcases an array of artifacts that reflect their rich traditions. Visitors can admire exquisite collections featuring traditional clothing, intricate horse gear, and ornate silver spurs alongside handmade leather items. The museum also houses a fascinating section dedicated to currency and accounting history on another floor.
name: Museo del Gaucho and Currency
address: Cerrito 351, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: City archives & historical artifacts displayed in an early 1800s colonial government building.
detail_description: The Museo Histórico Cabildo de Montevideo is a significant historical site located in the heart of Montevideo, Uruguay. Housed in an early 1800s colonial government building, it showcases city archives and historical artifacts. The iconic neo-classical structure features beautiful Doric and Ionic columns and holds great historical importance as the place where the first constitution of the Republic of Uruguay was promulgated in 1830.
name: Museo Histórico Cabildo de Montevideo
address: Juan Carlos Gómez 1362, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Sprawling green space with boating, amusement park rides & pergolas of roses, plus a restaurant.
detail_description: Prado Park, situated in the town of the same name, is Montevideo's largest urban park, covering over 100 hectares. The park offers a variety of attractions including boating, amusement park rides, rose gardens, and an agricultural market with local foods and handicrafts. Visitors can also explore landmarks such as the Obelisk and Covered Wagon monument while taking in the picturesque surroundings of tree-lined streets and historic homes from the early 1900s.
name: Prado Park
address: 4QVV+5CV, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: El Mingus is a trendy jazz bar located in the hipster district of Cordon Soho in Montevideo. The intimate club offers live jazz performances almost every night and serves delicious Mexican snacks and surprises. It's known for its inviting atmosphere and specialty drink, grappamiel, a beloved Uruguayan liquor made from grappa and honey. On Tuesdays, visitors can enjoy live jazz sessions that pair perfectly with the homemade grappamiel.
name: El Mingus
address: San Salvador 1952, 11200 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Jacinto is a renowned European-style restaurant located in the historic heart of Montevideo, Uruguay. Led by chef Lucia Soria, who trained under the famous Francis Mallmann, Jacinto offers a warm and inviting ambiance with marble-top tables, original brick ceilings, and large windows.
name: Jacinto
address: Sarandí 349, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: El Milongón Dinner Show offers an unforgettable evening filled with music, dance, delicious food, and delightful drinks. You can choose between the Copa Show for drinks and a show or the Cena Show for a multi-course dinner and entertainment. The talented dancers showcase captivating tango performances, folkloric songs, and regional dance styles like African Candombe. Located in Montevideo, this venue provides a unique experience where you can enjoy dinner while being entertained by tango and folklore shows.
name: El Milongón Cena Show
address: Gaboto 1812, 11800 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Located in the heart of Montevideo, Baar Fun Fun is a historic bar that has been operating since 1895. It offers a unique blend of live tango performances, delicious cocktails, and a lively atmosphere. The bar is known for its vintage lighting and soulful tango music that creates an atmosphere of camaraderie and revelry. It's a popular spot for locals and tourists to enjoy uvita shots and experience the classic South American vibe.
name: Baar Fun Fun
address: Sede CAF, Ciudadela 1229, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Mercado del Puerto is a popular spot in Independence Square, offering a variety of food options and souvenir shops. It's known for being a bit pricey, so be prepared to spend some money. The area also features the Cuidadela Gate and the Artigas Mausoleum, making it an excellent place to explore Uruguayan culture and history. Guides are knowledgeable about the city and provide insight into the country's politics and heritage.
name: Mercado del Puerto
address: Blvr. 26 de Marzo 3285, 11300 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Sarandí is a bustling pedestrian street that stretches from Puerta de la Ciudadela to the port, passing by the Cathedral and Plaza Constitucion. The street is lined with vendors selling traditional mates cups and handmade crafts, making it a great place to pick up unique souvenirs. It's also home to the only remaining section of the old city wall, adding a historical touch to its vibrant atmosphere.
name: Sarandí
address: 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Plaza Independencia, the main square in Montevideo, is a historic green space that features a mausoleum and monument dedicated to Jose Gervasio Artigas, a revered military leader. The mausoleum can be accessed through an underground staircase and houses Artigas' remains along with commemorative plaques.
name: Plaza Independencia
address: Statue of Artigas, Pl. Independencia, 11100 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: The Auditorio Nacional Adela Reta del SODRE is a modern venue located in the heart of Montevideo, just across from Plaza Independencia. It stands in contrast to the 19th-century Teatro Solis and offers a range of performances including opera, ballet, symphony, and chamber concerts. The auditorium boasts amazing acoustics and provides an excellent view of the stage.
name: Auditorio Nacional Adela Reta del SODRE
address: Andes 1459, 11100 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Neoclassical former seat of Uruguayan government & museum with exhibits on presidential history.
detail_description: Palacio Estevez, also known as Museo de la Casa de Gobierno, is a neoclassical building that served as the original seat of the Uruguayan government. Today, it houses a museum dedicated to the country's presidential history. Visitors can explore exhibits featuring historical artifacts and stories from Uruguay's post-colonial era up to 1967. The museum offers insights into the nation's early leaders and their contributions, as well as the electoral process.
name: Palacio Estevez | Museo de la Casa de Gobierno
address: Estévez Palace, Pl. Independencia 776, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Visual arts museum since 1911 featuring works by many Uruguayan artists & an outdoor sculpture park.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant Parque Rodo quarter, the National Museum of Visual Arts has been a cultural gem since its establishment in 1911. This museum showcases an extensive collection of Uruguayan visual art, featuring renowned artists like Pedro Figari and Juan Manuel Blanes. Visitors can explore various exhibition halls that host both national and international displays throughout the year. Additionally, the museum boasts an impressive art library with over 7,000 volumes, attracting scholars from around the world.
name: National Museum Of Visual Arts
address: Av Tomas Giribaldi 2283, 11300 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

name: Carrasco International Airport
address: 5X7M+5G8, Ruta 101-Capitan Juan Antonio Artigas, 14000 Ciudad de la Costa, Departamento de Canelones, Uruguay

name: Librería Puro Verso
address: Av. 18 de Julio 1199, 11100 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Av. 18 de Julio is a bustling avenue that showcases an eclectic mix of architectural styles, from colonial to Art Deco and even 1970s towers juxtaposed with elegant turn-of-the-century palaces. The diverse blend of buildings along this vibrant street offers a captivating glimpse into the city's rich architectural history.
name: Av. 18 de Julio
address: Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

name: Museo del Cannabis
address: Durazno 1784, 11200 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Bustling indoor mall offering apparel, shoes, grocery items, a movie theater & fast food outlets.
detail_description: Montevideo Shopping Center, the first mall in Montevideo, is a bustling indoor destination offering a wide array of shopping options. With over 180 stores, it houses national and international brands for clothing, tech accessories, home goods, and more. Located in the Buceo neighborhood, this modern center also features cinemas and restaurants. The area around the mall is vibrant day and night with cultural attractions and dining options. Additionally, it's conveniently situated within walking distance from various accommodations.
name: Montevideo Shopping Center
address: Av. Luis Alberto de Herrera 1290, 11300 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Montevideo, the Museo de la Memoria stands as a poignant reminder of Uruguay's tumultuous past during the civilian-military dictatorship from 1973 to 1985. Opened in 2007, this evocative museum is situated in the former summer residence of dictator Maximo Santos and serves as a vital space for reflection on human rights and social justice.
name: Museo de la Memoria
address: Av. de las Instrucciones 1057, 12900 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Relaxed city destination popular for walks along the beach & promenade, plus sunset views.
detail_description: Playa Ramirez is a relaxed city destination known for its beautiful beach and promenade, offering stunning sunset views. Located near downtown and Rodo Park, this 1.4-kilometer crescent along La Rambla provides various activities on the sand and in the calm waters, making it perfect for families. The area also features bars, cafes, restaurants, hotels, and the National Museum of Visual Arts.
name: Playa Ramirez
address: Montevideo Department, Uruguay

excerpt: Bookstore & coffeehouse in a classy 1903 building with workshops, readings & cultural events.
detail_description: Escaramuza is a charming bookstore and coffeehouse housed in a historic 1903 building. It offers a variety of cultural events, workshops, and readings. The café serves delectable treats like cheese scones, savory pies filled with spinach or beetroot, and an array of sweets made from seasonal ingredients. Additionally, the bookstore boasts a well-stocked collection of limited-edition Spanish-language titles.
name: Escaramuza
address: Dr. Pablo de María 1185, 11200 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay

detail_description: The Mirador Panorámico de la Intendencia de Montevideo offers a 360-degree view of the city and the La Plata River from nearly 80 meters above ground. Located on the 22nd floor of the Edificio Sede de la Intendencia, visitors can enjoy stunning vistas of Montevideo's skyline, including prominent landmarks like Torre ANTEL and the World Trade Center towers.
name: Mirador panorámico de la Intendencia de Montevideo
address: Soriano 1372, S. José 1351, 11200 Montevideo, Uruguay

excerpt: Prado is a quiet, upscale residential district known for the sprawling park of the same name, where visitors stroll among native and exotic plants in the Botanical Garden and roses planted around stone arches in El Rosedal. There are more landscaped gardens at Museo Blanes, a 19th-century villa now a museum for Uruguayan art. Las Carmelitas is a much-photographed, 1920s-built church resembling Paris’s Notre Dame.
detail_description: Prado is a serene and elegant residential area that boasts the expansive Prado Park, featuring the Botanical Garden with its diverse plant species and El Rosedal adorned with roses. The district also houses Museo Blanes, a former 19th-century villa transformed into a museum showcasing Uruguayan art. Additionally, Las Carmelitas, an iconic church reminiscent of Paris's Notre Dame, stands as a popular photography spot.
name: Prado
address: Montevideo, Montevideo Department, Uruguay

detail_description: The museum LA CUMPARSITA Dinner & Tango Show is a great place to learn about tango. There are exhibits with photos, videos, and other artifacts from the history of tango. The dinner show features dancers performing traditional Argentine dances like the milonga and the pasodoble.
name: MUSEO DEL TANGO - Tours & Tango show
address: Pl. Independencia 846, 11000 Montevideo, Departamento de Montevideo, Uruguay
